<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[189,1399,1051,1190]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
We follow the definition of the genus given in the key to the genera of Hemisphaeriini proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Sun Y. &amp; Meng R. &amp; Wang Y." journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" pagination="42 - 53" part="3186" refString="Sun Y., Meng R. &amp; Wang Y. 2012. Neogergithoides, a new genus with a new species from China (Hemiptera: Issidae). Zootaxa 3186: 42 - 53." title="Neogergithoides, a new genus with a new species from China (Hemiptera: Issidae)" type="journal article" year="2012">
Sun 
<emphasis box="[189,248,1089,1115]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">et al.</emphasis>
(2012)
</bibRefCitation>
, with the following distinctive set of characters: (1) posterior wing longer than half length of tegmen; (2) frons with complete median carina; (3) lateral margins of frons not elevated and (4) a row of tubercles along lateral margin of frons.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[189,248,1232,1258]" box="[189,248,1232,1258]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,248,1232,1258]" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" reason="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,248,1232,1258]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Note</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[189,1399,1280,1457]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<bibRefCitation author="Ishihara T." box="[189,385,1280,1307]" journalOrPublisher="Special Bulletin of the Lepidoptera Society of Japan" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" pagination="201 - 221" part="1" refString="Ishihara T. 1965 a. Some species of Formosan Homoptera. Special Bulletin of the Lepidoptera Society of Japan 1: 201 - 221." title="Some species of Formosan Homoptera" type="journal article" year="1965" yearSuffix="a">Ishihara (1965a)</bibRefCitation>
was the first to propose 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Matsumura" authorityYear="1916" box="[689,787,1281,1306]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cottidae" genus="Daruma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpaeniformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[689,787,1281,1306]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Daruma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schumacher" authorityYear="1915" box="[1088,1240,1280,1306]" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Gergithoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1088,1240,1280,1306]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Gergithoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, although he should have used the name 
<taxonomicName authority="Metcalf, 1952" authorityName="Metcalf" authorityYear="1952" box="[533,657,1319,1344]" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Darumara" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[533,657,1319,1344]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Darumara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as proposed by Metclaf (1952). It seems that 
<bibRefCitation author="Chan M. - L. &amp; Yang C. - T." journalOrPublisher="National Chung Hsing University, Department of Entomology, Taichung (Taiwan)" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" refString="Chan M. - L. &amp; Yang C. - T. 1994. Issidae of Taiwan (Homoptera: Fulgoroidea). National Chung Hsing University, Department of Entomology, Taichung (Taiwan)." title="Issidae of Taiwan (Homoptera: Fulgoroidea)" type="book" year="1994">Chan &amp; Yang (1994)</bibRefCitation>
were not aware of Ishihara’s (1965a) synonymy, as they considered 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schumacher" authorityYear="1915" box="[1066,1218,1355,1381]" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Gergithoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1066,1218,1355,1381]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Gergithoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Metcalf, 1952" authorityName="Metcalf" authorityYear="1952" box="[1275,1399,1356,1381]" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Darumara" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1275,1399,1356,1381]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Darumara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as separate genera. More recently, 
<bibRefCitation author="Gnezdilov V. M." box="[595,802,1393,1419]" journalOrPublisher="Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" pagination="75 - 92" part="49" refString="Gnezdilov V. M. 2009. Revisionary notes on some tropical Issidae and Nogodinidae (Hemiptera: Fulgoroidea). Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae 49 (1): 75 - 92." title="Revisionary notes on some tropical Issidae and Nogodinidae (Hemiptera: Fulgoroidea)" type="journal article" year="2009">Gnezdilov (2009)</bibRefCitation>
reinstated Ishihara’s (1965a) view but erroneously stated that he proposed a new synonymy instead.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
