<paragraph blockId="3.[189,303,1877,1903]" box="[189,303,1877,1903]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,1877,1903]" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" reason="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,1877,1903]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[189,1398,1926,2027]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
The species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schumacher" authorityYear="1915" box="[373,525,1926,1952]" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Gergithoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[373,525,1926,1952]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Gergithoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be identified based on the comparison of the male genitalia with reliable illustrations. Considering the numerous pending issues regarding the identity of the species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schumacher" authorityYear="1915" box="[189,341,2001,2027]" class="Insecta" family="Issidae" genus="Gergithoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[189,341,2001,2027]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Gergithoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it is currently unwise to propose an identification key to the species.
</paragraph>
